Two MP hopefuls have said they have been the de facto Rongo legislators without pay following incumbent Dalmas Otieno&rsquo;s (pictured) long absence.Paul Abuor and Ong&rsquo;ono Ng&rsquo;an lost in the 2013 polls. They said they have attended most ODM functions in his absence for close to two years.The two spoke on Monday during the opening of the East Kamagambo ward party offices.